the downloads needed

```bash
go get github.com/joho/godotenv

go get github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5
go get github.com/gorilla/mux
go get gorm.io/gorm
go get gorm.io/driver/postgres

go get golang.org/x/oauth2@v0.28.0
go get golang.org/x/oauth2/google

```

run:
```bash
docker build -t auth-service .
docker run -p 8080:8080 --env-file .env auth-service
```

how to test

1. jwt
  Login to get a token:
  method: POST
  url: http://localhost:8080/login
  headers: {Content-Type: application/json}
  body: {
    "username":"admin",
    "password":"1234"
  }
  Expected success response:{
  "token": (token)
}
  use token:
  method: GET

url: http://localhost:8080/protected

headers: { Authorization: Bearer (the token you got)}
Expected result (from terminal): Hello, admin! You accessed a protected route.


2. oauth
on any browser, head to http://localhost:8080/oauth2-login